<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-15T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-15T12:00:00-05:00" n="145" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d145">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3731/908: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-15T12:00:00-05:00">August 15,
                                1934—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>394. My telegram 380, August 10, noon. Cuban officials state they desire
                            reduction of consular fees “on and after July 1, 1935.”since estimated
                            receipts (difference of over one million pesos) included in this year’s
                            budget.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>